| 1 | Server-side template injection and stored XSS | `/profile`, the f-string HTML plus `render_template_string(html)` | Critical | If `user[1]`, `user[2]`, or `user[3]` contains `{{ config }}`, `{{ cycler.__init__.__globals__.os.popen(...) }}`, or `<script>...</script>`, it is inserted into the template source before Jinja renders it. That can become SSTI/RCE or stored XSS. | Never build templates with f-strings containing user data. Use a real template or pass variables into Jinja. |
| 2 | No authentication / authorization on money transfer | `/transfer` | Critical | Anyone can POST `sender=1&recipient=attacker&amount=1000` and move funds from any account. The client controls the sender. | Require login, derive sender from the authenticated session/JWT, and verify recipient/account permissions. |
| 3 | CSRF on money transfer | `/transfer` | High | A malicious site can submit a hidden form to `/transfer` from a victim’s browser if they are logged in. | Enable CSRF protection, e.g. `Flask-WTF CSRFProtect`, and validate CSRF tokens. |
| 4 | Negative or invalid transfer amount | `/transfer` | High | Posting `amount=-1000` reverses the debit/credit logic, increasing the sender balance and decreasing the recipient balance. `NaN`/`inf` may also cause logic errors. | Parse with `Decimal`, reject non-positive and non-finite amounts, enforce limits. |
| 5 | No balance/atomicity checks for transfer | `/transfer` | High | A user can overdraw an account because the code subtracts without checking balance. Partial or concurrent updates can create inconsistent state. | Perform the transfer in one transaction with a sufficient-balance condition and verify affected rows. |
| 6 | Path traversal / arbitrary file read | `/download` | Critical | Requesting `/download?file=../../etc/passwd` can escape `DOWNLOAD_DIR` and read local files accessible to the app. | Use `send_from_directory` plus `safe_join`, reject absolute paths and traversal. |
| 7 | Insecure deserialization with `pickle.loads` | `/import` | Critical | An attacker can POST a crafted pickle payload that executes arbitrary Python code during deserialization. | Do not accept pickle from users. Use JSON or another safe format and validate schema. |
| 8 | Sensitive error disclosure | `/import` exception handler | Medium | Returning `str(e)` can reveal internal paths, DB details, parsing behavior, or stack-related clues useful for exploitation. | Log server-side; return a generic error. |
| 9 | Hardcoded JWT secret | `JWT_SECRET = "supersecret123"` | High | If this secret is used for signing JWTs, anyone with source access or a leaked repo can forge tokens. The value is weak and static. | Load a strong secret from environment or a secret manager. |
| 10 | Debug mode enabled | `app.run(debug=True)` | High/Critical in exposed environments | Flask debugger can expose interactive execution if reachable and the PIN is bypassed/leaked. It also leaks stack traces. | Never run debug mode in production. Use environment-gated config. |

